  <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_NamingConventions> a narr:Digest ;
    narr:digestOf <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#NamingConventions> ;
    narr:childCount "41"^^xsd:integer ;
    narr:generatedFrom "d1b09a828565de86" ;
    narr:narration """This hub gathers aswritten's running naming pass — tool, tier, and service renames driven by one constraint: the word must live in the writing/language/knowledge space and capture a whole perspective, not a data package ([naming constraints and direction](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_NamingConstraints)). Earliest (Mar 17): [tier named 'Professional' over 'Enterprise'](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ProfessionalOverEnterprise), defined by service level not org size. Mar 19 opened the bigger sweep — [annotate flagged for cite/provenance/source](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_AnnotateRename), the [internal marketplace named 'catalogue'](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_CatalogueInternalMarketplace). Mar 31 firmed the literal-description logic: [distillation → perspective creation](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_DistillationToPerspectiveCreation), the cascading [perspective=ID → id=ID param fix](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_IDParameterRename), and 'consult' [freed as a general word](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_ConsultTermFreed). Apr 16 added a pitch-language rule: [say 'create a perspective', never 'train'](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_CreatePerspectiveNotTrain). Alongside the decisions sits a thick layer of brand-stylization style observations (lowercase 'aswritten', backticked tool names, → as a flow operator, coined terms like worldview graph). The through-line is a metaphor-to-literal shift; several names remain explicitly open.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_AnnotateRename> ;
